{"id": 5336, "title": "Ticket #5336: Have ubertickets age out or get cleaned up on the SchedD side.", "description": "<blockquote>\nWhen a user is no longer running or submitting jobs, their uberticket and other credentials should be cleaned up.  I'm proposing a \"mark and sweep\" approach.  When the schedd notices the last job for a user leave the queue, it signals the CredD (either directly via a daemoncore command, or indirectly by dropping a .flag file in the SEC_CRED_DIR) and the CredD is the responsible for cleaning up the marked files after X minutes.  Anytime a new credential is stored, existing marks are removed.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Oct-24 11:16</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/83be200fd421939114d1b0c53f589bb1a30e4ea4\">[46101]</a></span>: Create \"mark\" file when a user no longer has jobs in the queue <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5336\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5336'); return false;\" title=\"Have ubertickets age out or get cleaned up on the SchedD side.\">#5336</a></span>  (By zmiller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Oct-23 21:08</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/6da070736777c21cc18cee32b07289d6840d6cae\">[46100]</a></span>: Consolidate code for clearing \"mark\" files. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wik